regarding re reconstruction reperformance research events at stanford regarding re reconstruction reperformance research facebook twitter email print add to calendar over the past few years the repetition of live performance has returned as a central problem for performance studies art history and theater studies as the plastic and performing arts industries revisit landmark performances of the 1960s and 1970s artists and scholars have posed questions about the function validity and ontology of such reperformances bringing together some of the most distinguished scholars and artists in the fields of art dance and theater this conference returns to these questions emphasizing the role of creativity in reconstruction and exploring how it works as both pedagogy and research rsvp required regardingre gmail com mini conference schedule friday 3.00 4.30 opening remarks keynote by amelia jones 5.00 6.00 class showing reperformance of american moon by robert whitman invitation only saturday 9.30 10.30 address by marin blazevic 10.45 12.15 keynote by mark franko 12.30 2.00 roundtable with robert whitman and student performers lunch will be provided 2.00 3.00 address by mario biagini when ongoing every day from february 17 2012 through february 18 2012 where levinthal hall stanford humanities center map audience general public faculty staff students tags arts conference symposium sponsor humanities center department of drama stanford institute for creativity and the arts vice provost for undergraduate education contact dramainfo stanford edu admission open to all stanford university faculty staff and students with the exception of the reperformance of the american moon on friday 5 6pm by separate invitation only permalink http events stanford edu events 307 30753 more info last modified february 14 2012
